<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-12T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-12T08:00:00-05:00" n="845" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d845">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7490F/12–1244: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-12T14:00:00+01:00">December 12, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received December 12—noon.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>11006. ReDept’s 9918, November 25, 6 p.m. and 10264 December 8, 3
                                    p.m.<note n="7" xml:id="d845fn7">Latter not printed.</note>
                                Department’s views were presented personally by me to Mr. Eden. In
                                order to be able to reply fully Eden is consulting Foreign Office
                                officials who are directly concerned with certain aspects of this
                                matter. I expect soon to be able to telegraph Eden’s reply.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>